RIYADH: Saudi Foreign Minister Prince Faisal bin Farhan received Tut Galwak, security affairs advisor of South Sudan President Salva Kiir, in Riyadh on Sunday. During the meeting, the two sides reviewed bilateral relations and ways to enhance, develop and advance them to broader horizons in various fields. Both sides also exchanged views on regional and international issues of common interest. The reception was attended by Saudi Assistant Minister of State for African Countries Affairs Dr. Sami Al-Saleh. 